President Obama announced his intent to nominate Todd Phillip Haskell as Ambassador to the Republic of the Congo and Jason E. Kearns as a Member of the U.S. International Trade Commission. He also announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key Administration posts, including Adrienne Harris and Behnaz Kibria as Members of the Advisory Committee for Trade Policy and Negotiations, and Erica Schwartz as a Member of the Board of Visitors to the United States Merchant Marine Academy. President Obama expressed confidence in these individuals' experience and dedication to their roles.